<head>PREJUDICE</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>PRECONCEIVED IDEA</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">偏見</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>INTENSELY BELIEVED OPINION, TYPICALLY MISTAKEN, LACKING PROOF.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>朱熹 : 灌去舊見, 以來新意.</p>
        </div>
<div type="old-chinese-contrasts">
<p>The question of Chinese notions of Prejudice is closely connected with that of rationality. The history of the notion in the West must be traced carefully, and compared with Chinese conceptual developments in the same conceptual area.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
